17/11/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- During his visit to Bucharest on Thursday (November 16th), NATO Secretary-General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer praised Romania for setting a good example of NATO member state participation in peacekeeping operations.He met with President Traian Basescu, Foreign Minister Mihai-Razvan Ungureanu and Defence Minister Sorin Frunzaverde as part of an ongoing tour, in preparation for the NATO summit in Riga at the end of the month. They discussed the need for an open-door policy, trans-Atlantic solidarity and dialogue, NATO operations -- particularly in Kosovo and Afghanistan -- and the situation in the Western Balkans. (Mediafax, Rompres - 16/11/06)
